body:
Hi, 

I have a use case similar, but not exactly the same as what was reported and fixed in #1315:

The following works (example from #1315):
```
module ex24
 (
   input wire i_clk,
   input wire i_rst_n
 );
   parameter int SIZES [3:0] = '{1,2,3,4};
   typedef int calc_sums_t [3:0];
   function calc_sums_t calc_sums;
     begin
       int ii, sum = 0;
       for (ii=0; ii<4; ii++) begin
        sum = sum + SIZES[ii];
        calc_sums[ii] = sum;
       end
     end
   endfunction
   parameter int SUMS[3:0] = calc_sums();
 endmodule
```
The following does not:
```
module ex24
 (
   input wire i_clk,
   input wire i_rst_n
 );
   parameter int SIZES [3:0] = '{1,2,3,4};
   typedef int calc_sums_t [3:0];
   function calc_sums_t calc_sums(int s[], int n);
     begin
       int ii, sum = 0;
       for (ii=0; ii<n; ii++) begin
        sum = sum + n[ii];
        calc_sums[ii] = sum;
       end
     end
   endfunction
   parameter int SUMS[3:0] = calc_sums(SIZES, 4);
 endmodule
```
The Error messages:
```
%Error: ex24.sv:37:40: Expecting expression to be constant, but variable isn't const: 'SIZES'
                    : ... In instance ex24
   37 |    parameter int SUMS[3:0] = calc_sums(SIZES, 4);
      |                                        ^~~~~
%Error: Internal Error: ex24.sv:37:40: ../V3Simulate.h:294: No value found for node.
                                    : ... In instance our
   37 |    parameter int SUMS[3:0] = calc_sums(SIZES, 4);
      |                                        ^~~~~
```
Is this expected behavior? 

I am happy to help, if I can (I am not familiar with the codebase).
